Items.name: Strawberry
Items.origin: Various regions including Europe, North America, and Asia
Items.benefits: Strawberries are rich in antioxidants, vitamins, and fiber. They may help improve heart health, regulate blood sugar levels, and reduce inflammation.

Items.name: Apple
Items.origin: Various regions including North America, Europe, and Asia
Items.benefits: Apples are rich in antioxidants, vitamins, and dietary fiber. They may help improve heart health, aid in digestion, and lower the risk of chronic diseases.

Items.name: Banana
Items.origin: Tropical regions, including Southeast Asia and Africa
Items.benefits: Bananas are rich in potassium, vitamins, and antioxidants. They may help improve digestion, regulate blood pressure, and boost energy levels.

Items.name: Grapes
Items.origin: Various regions including Europe, North America, and Asia
Items.benefits: Grapes are high in antioxidants, vitamins, and minerals. They may support heart health, improve immune function, and aid in digestion.

Items.name: Orange
Items.origin: Various regions including Florida, California, and Mediterranean countries
Items.benefits: Oranges are rich in vitamin C, fiber, and antioxidants. They may boost immune function, support skin health, and aid in digestion.

Items.name: Blueberry
Items.origin: Various regions including North America and Europe
Items.benefits: Blueberries are packed with antioxidants, vitamins, and fiber. They may improve brain function, promote heart health, and help regulate blood sugar levels.
